data.text: @redcloud_scribe Yeah exactly, how could I forget the factor of unknown cases that just layers on more and more dread to the situation. Truly bananas either way.

@ChrisMBowling Obviously we are also missing cases now, what with rapid tests not being reported and all. But yeah, taking both numbers by 5x and estimating that as the true infection level is shocking.

@ChrisMBowling to get even more into the weeds on this, because I'm that guy...the actual number in January (as opposed to  positive test #) would have been so incredibly high. I have seen estimates that the US was catching between 10-20% of (?!) Omicron cases in January. So...maybe 3,000!
@Bacon_Dick Covid was no match against the pipeline
@ChrisMBowling was thinking about this yesterday, crazy how in NE at least it feels like COVID has completely vanished
